    <h1>Pass law and make it clear</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200925/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-25"><time>2020-09-25</time></a>
        - <span>FORUM</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Be­fore we go on about met­ing out penal­ties for not re­turn­ing trays, please pass a law clar­i­fy­ing that one has to do so af­ter eat­ing (Time to pe­nalise those not re­turn­ing trays at food cen­tres, by Mr Ang Tun Loon, Sept 22)</p>
    <p>Without a clear rul­ing, please don’t ex­pect the gen­eral public to be civic minded.</p>
    <p>Right now it is sort of “up to you” be­cause there isn’t a clear man­date. Make it clear and we as a so­ci­ety will ad­here to the law. Ong Hock Cheng</p>
    <p>Without a clear rul­ing, please don’t ex­pect the gen­eral public to be civic minded.</p>


